race.comment: OLD MATE HENRY (11) ended last campaign in impressive fashion, winning two on end, albeit over further. He has placed in both fresh efforts and while his trial looks plain on numbers, his late work was very impressive. Has strong claims from a good draw and with Noske on board. URQUHARTS BLUFF (10) steps out to 1400m for the first time after a 1.7L defeat last time out. The rise in trip doesn't look an issue on what he's done recently and he has enough early speed to offset the tricky gate. Can bounce back to winning ways. DE GRANDHOMME (1) is another who steps out to 1400m for the first time, just missing when racing over 1100m last time out. Nottle hops on board now and if he can handle the rise in trip, he can play a leading role. YOUGIVEMECHILLS (13) was too good last time out, scoring impressively over this course and distance. This is tougher, though the fresh win rates highly and another forward showing is expected. RALLY THE TROOPS (5) is never far away.
